affinity mapping --> grouping your insights by common themes or categories --> 

1
one observation per post-it note--> quotes behavoirs, likes, and dilikes from worksheet 

2
place observations into groupings based on similarities and trends 

3 step back 
refine and rename your groupings as many times as neede until the insights emerge 

____________________________________
color coding of insights -> info that we have 

tips for sucess 
looking for opportunites not solutions 

in this stage, you want to keep the thinking broad so you can explore as many angles as possible 

write down what it is you have, not what you want or what needs to happen 

AFFINITY MAPPING 

weak groupings 

groups with too few data point sare weak 
groups with too many data point are weak 
groups formed enirely by data from one user is weak 
weak groupings suggest that more research is needed 

collaboration --> GOOGLE DESIGN SPRINT 

use affinity mapping to share and synthesize data from multiple sources 

work silentyl to allow each teamets perspective to be reflected by the diagram 

any group that the entire team cant abide by should be reorganized

